The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Azureus lifts main event 

 STAR RACER

 Calcutta: 

 Trainer Vijay Singhs youngster Azureus displayed 

 brilliant form to clinch the 1,400m Independence Cup, a 

 sweepstakes which was the main attraction in Saturdays 

 eight-event race card. In his debut run, the China Visit-Treasure 

 Land colt had thrashed a good field in Western India but 

 subsequently failed during the Bangalore summer season. 

 Suraj Narredu, who partnered the winner, also helped the 

 trainer score a treble. The duos other winners were 

 Silver Fox and Flemenco Star who had the measure of the 

 favourite, Imperial Stride, the Swatantrata Cup also a 

 sweepsatakes. Trainer Daniel David, too, saddled three winners 

 on the day but the third sweepstakes, the Wiseman Cup, was 

 claimed by Vrikodara, a Shafiq Khan-trained horse.

